{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddca4e299-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1833b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1833b"},"text":"§ 1833b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Comparability in compensation schedules","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"iddca4e29a-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1833b/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation, the Comptroller of the Currency, the National Credit Union Administration Board, the Federal Housing Finance Agency, the Office of Financial Research, and the Bureau of Consumer Financial Protection, the ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002275"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002275"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be “Research, the Bureau of Consumer Financial Protection, and the”."}],"tail":" Farm Credit Administration, in establishing and adjusting schedules of compensation and benefits which are to be determined solely by each agency under applicable provisions of law, shall inform the heads of the other agencies and the Congress of such compensation and benefits and shall seek to maintain comparability regarding compensation and benefits."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"iddca4e29b-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1833b/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Commodity Futures Trading Commission","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In establishing and adjusting schedules of compensation and benefits for employees of the Commodity Futures Trading Commission under applicable provisions of law, the Commission shall—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddca4e29c-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1833b/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" inform the heads of the agencies referred to in subsection (a) and Congress of such compensation and benefits; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddca4e29d-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1833b/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" seek to maintain comparability with those agencies regarding compensation and benefits.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddca4e29e-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/73/tXII/s1206"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–73, title XII, § 1206","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-08-09"},"text":"Aug. 9, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/523"},"text":"103 Stat. 523","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/233/tIII/s302/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–233, title III, § 302(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-12-12"},"text":"Dec. 12, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/1767"},"text":"105 Stat. 1767","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/123/s8/d/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–123, § 8(d)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-01-16"},"text":"Jan. 16, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/115/2400"},"text":"115 Stat. 2400","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/171/tX/s10702/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–171, title X, § 10702(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-05-13"},"text":"May 13, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/516"},"text":"116 Stat. 516","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203/tI/s152/d/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203, title I, § 152(d)(3)","children":[],"tail":", title III, § 367(8), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-07-21"},"text":"July 21, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/1414"},"text":"124 Stat. 1414","children":[],"tail":", 1557.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddca4e29f-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddca4e2a0-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"iddca4e2a1-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Financial Institutions Reform, Recovery, and Enforcement Act of 1989, and not as part of the Federal Deposit Insurance Act which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"iddca4e2a2-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2010—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203/s367/8/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203, § 367(8)(B)","children":[],"tail":", which directed striking out “, and the Office of Thrift Supervision” could not be executed because those words did not appear subsequent to amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203/s152/d/3/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203, § 152(d)(3)(B)","children":[],"tail":". See below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203/s367/8/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203, § 367(8)(A)","children":[],"tail":", which directed substitution of “Agency, and” for “Board, the Oversight Board of the Resolution Trust Corporation”, was executed by substituting “Agency” for “Board” after “Federal Housing Finance”, to reflect the probable intent of Congress and the amendments made by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/123"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–123","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/233/s302/a"},"text":"section 302(a) of Pub. L. 102–233","children":[],"tail":". See 2002 Amendment note and Change of Name note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/203/s152/d/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–203, § 152(d)(3)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Finance Board, the Office of Financial Research, and the Bureau of Consumer Financial Protection” for “Finance Board,” and struck out “and the Office of Thrift Supervision,” after “Credit Administration,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/171"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–171","children":[],"tail":" designated existing provisions as subsec. (a), inserted heading, and added subsec. (b)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/123"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–123","children":[],"tail":" struck out “the Thrift Depositor Protection Oversight Board of the Resolution Trust Corpora